---
permalink: /index.xsl
layout: feed.xsl.liquid
description: Stream of all the latest content published on tommi.space
---
<main>
	<div class='half'>
		{% render 'wtfeed.liquid', lang: lang %}
	</div>
	<article class='half yellow box subgrid'>
		<h2 class='span-3'>Who created this?</h2>
		<figure class='span-1 flex'>
			{% img 'profile.webp', 'Tommi on stage conducting a live show' %}</img>
		</figure>
		<div class='span-2'>
			{% renderTemplate 'md' %}
				Hey, I’m <span class='p-name'>Tommi</span>. In one word, I am an <strong class='p-category p-label'>enthusiast</strong>. Who I am is best represented by the manifesto of my being, or <cite>[Tomminess](/tomminess 'Tomminess — tommi.space')</cite>.

				I am in perpetual movement, and I get involved in <a href='/tutto' hreflang='it' title='A log of all that I do'>a lot of stuff</a>. Hence, I can really relate to what <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gottfried_Wilhelm_Leibniz' title='Leibniz on Wikipedia'>Leibniz</a> said: <q cite='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gottfried_Wilhelm_Leibniz'>in my life I started everything and concluded nothing</q>.
			{% endrenderTemplate %}
		</div>
	</article>
	<article class='half box'>
		<h2>Sub-feeds</h2>
		<p>Click on the buttons below to go to the feeds related to specific languages or categories.</p>
		<div class='flex'>
			<a class='it button' href='/it.xml' hreflang='it' title='Italian-only content feed'>Italian</a>
			<a class='blue button' href='/zibaldone.xml' hreflang='it' title='Blog posts feed (mainly in Italian)'>Zibaldone</a>
			<a class='razzmatazz button' href='/jam.xml' title='Feed from “The Jam”, Tommi’s notes'>The Jam</a>
			<a class='pasticci button' href='/poetry.xml' hreflang='it' title='Feed of poems I wrote'>Poetry</a>
			<a class='idea button' href='/ideas.xml' title='Impromptu and ideas feed'>Ideas</a>
			<a class='reading button' href='/reading.xml' title='Reading notes'>Reading</a>
		</div>
	</article>
	<article class='half blue box'>
		<h2>Data-based feeds</h2>
		<p>The following feeds are not generated by pages or posts published on this website, but rather by streams of data.</p>
		<div class='flex'>
			<a class='yellow written button' href='/activities.xml' title='Activities I am attending/hosting'>Activities</a>
			<a class='red written button' href='/internet-awesomeness.xml' title='Feed of the awesome things I stumble upon while surfing the ’net'>Internet Awesomeness</a>
		</div>
	</article>
	<div class='wide center flex'>
		<h2 class='wavyBackgroundRed'>The latest things published on tommi.space</h2>
	</div>
	<div class='wide grid'>
		<xsl:for-each select='/rss/channel/item'>
			<a><xsl:attribute name='href'><xsl:value-of select='link'/></xsl:attribute>
				<div class='little box'>
					<h3><xsl:value-of select='title'/></h3>
					<p><time><xsl:value-of select='pubDate' /></time></p>
				</div>
			</a>
		</xsl:for-each>
	</div>
</main>

